---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Himanshu Arora | AroraMSP · M365 Security & Entra ID"
  description="Microsoft 365 security, Intune, and Entra ID for enterprise IT teams. Real production experience, documented from the field — scripts, fixes, and root causes from 11+ years in the Microsoft ecosystem."
  page="home"
  canonical="https://aroramsp.com/"
  ogTitle="AroraMSP - Microsoft 365 Consulting"
  ogDescription="Independent Microsoft 365 consulting. Tenant security audits, Entra ID, Conditional Access, Exchange Online, and Intune for organizations globally."
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" slot="head" is:raw>
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@graph": [
      {
        "@type": "Person",
        "@id": "https://aroramsp.com/#himanshu-arora",
        "name": "Himanshu Arora",
        "url": "https://aroramsp.com/",
        "jobTitle": "Independent Microsoft 365 Consultant",
        "description": "Independent Microsoft 365 consultant with 11+ years in the Microsoft ecosystem. Specialising in tenant security audits, Entra ID, Conditional Access, Exchange Online, Intune, and PowerShell automation.",
        "knowsAbout": [
          "Microsoft 365 security",
          "Microsoft Intune",
          "Microsoft Entra ID",
          "Conditional Access",
          "Exchange Online",
          "Microsoft Graph PowerShell",
          "Windows LAPS",
          "Tenant security audits",
          "Hybrid identity",
          "AD Connect"
        ],
        "sameAs": [
          "https://linkedin.com/in/himanshusac",
          "https://github.com/hiaror"
        ]
      },
      {
        "@type": "ProfessionalService",
        "@id": "https://aroramsp.com/#org",
        "name": "AroraMSP",
        "url": "https://aroramsp.com/",
        "logo": "https://aroramsp.com/uploads/arora_msp_favicon.svg",
        "image": "https://aroramsp.com/uploads/og-preview.png",
        "description": "Independent Microsoft 365 consulting. Tenant security audits, Entra ID, Conditional Access, Exchange Online, Intune deployment, and PowerShell automation for organisations globally.",
        "founder": { "@id": "https://aroramsp.com/#himanshu-arora" },
        "areaServed": "Worldwide",
        "serviceType": [
          "Microsoft 365 tenant security audit",
          "Microsoft Intune deployment",
          "Microsoft Entra ID configuration",
          "Conditional Access policy design",
          "Exchange Online migration",
          "PowerShell automation"
        ]
      },
      {
        "@type": "WebSite",
        "@id": "https://aroramsp.com/#website",
        "url": "https://aroramsp.com/",
        "name": "AroraMSP",
        "publisher": { "@id": "https://aroramsp.com/#org" }
      }
    ]
  }
  </script>

  <section class="hero-page wrap" style="min-height: calc(100vh - var(--nav-h) - 150px); display:flex; align-items:center; padding-top: 12px; padding-bottom: 12px;">
    <div class="hero-grid">
      <div>
        <div class="eyebrow reveal">
          <span class="pulse"></span>
          <span>Available worldwide · accepting new clients</span>
        </div>
        <picture class="reveal reveal-delay-1">
          <source srcset="/himanshu-arora.webp" type="image/webp" />
          <img src="/himanshu-arora.png" alt="Himanshu Arora" class="hero-headshot" width="111" height="111" />
        </picture>
        <h1 class="headline">
          Microsoft 365 security, Intune, and Entra ID<br />
          for <span class="accent accent-gradient">enterprise IT</span> teams.
        </h1>
        <p class="hero-tag reveal reveal-delay-2">// real production experience, documented from the field, so you skip the trial and error.</p>
        <p class="hero-lede reveal reveal-delay-3">
          Himanshu Arora has spent 11+ years in the Microsoft ecosystem — from frontline
          cloud support at a Microsoft vendor to delivering enterprise-grade M365 security,
          Intune, and Entra ID projects for organisations globally. He documents everything:
          the real fixes, the actual scripts, and the root causes that never make it into
          the official docs.
        </p>
        <div class="cta-row reveal reveal-delay-4">
          <a href="https://outlook.office.com/bookwithme/user/583f5a3aa6e24f3fa36ea6bf9f4d2ba5@aroramsp.com/meetingtype/Vz8AH2J0jkiWmYCcAuw7bw2?anonymous&ismsaljsauthenabled&ep=mcard" class="btn btn-primary" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Book a free 30-min call <span class="arrow">→</span></a>
          <a href="/whatido" class="btn btn-ghost">What I do</a>
        </div>
        <div class="trust-row">
          <span class="t">11+ yrs Microsoft ecosystem</span>
          <span class="t">Senior Project Delivery Engineer</span>
          <span class="t">M365 / Intune / Entra ID</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div>
        <div class="terminal">
          <div class="terminal-bar">
            <div class="tb-dots"><span></span><span></span><span></span></div>
            <div class="tb-title">himanshu@aroramsp ~ %</div>
          </div>
          <div class="terminal-body" set:html={`<span class="m"># run a tenant health check</span>
<span class="line"><span class="p">$</span><span class="c">Connect-<span class="k">MgGraph</span> -Scopes <span class="s">"Directory.Read.All"</span></span></span>
<span class="line"><span class="m">  → auth ok · tenant: </span><span class="hl">contoso.onmicrosoft.com</span></span>

<span class="line"><span class="p">$</span><span class="c">Invoke-<span class="k">AroraAudit</span> -Scope <span class="s">All</span></span></span>
<span class="line"><span class="m">  ├─</span> <span class="ok">✓</span> MFA enforced              <span class="m">100%</span></span>
<span class="line"><span class="m">  ├─</span> <span class="w">!</span> Legacy auth enabled       <span class="w">3 users</span></span>
<span class="line"><span class="m">  ├─</span> <span class="w">!</span> SPF/DKIM/DMARC incomplete <span class="w">2 domains</span></span>
<span class="line"><span class="m">  ├─</span> <span class="ok">✓</span> Conditional access         <span class="ok">12 policies</span></span>
<span class="line"><span class="m">  └─</span> <span class="w">!</span> Unused E3 licenses         <span class="w">$4,320/yr</span></span>

<span class="line"><span class="m">→ generated report · </span><span class="hl">47 findings</span><span class="m"> · </span><span class="hl">12 quick wins</span></span>
<span class="line"><span class="p">$</span><span class="c">_</span><span class="cursor"></span></span>`} />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="stats-row wrap">
    <div class="stat-card reveal">
      <div class="stat-number">11+</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Years in Microsoft ecosystem</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card reveal reveal-delay-1">
      <div class="stat-number">9</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Years at a Microsoft vendor</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card reveal reveal-delay-2">
      <div class="stat-number">5</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Microsoft certifications</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card reveal reveal-delay-3">
      <div class="stat-number">6</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Open source tools published</div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="certs-row wrap reveal">
    <div class="cert-stat">
      <img src="/badges/microsoft-certified-expert-badge.svg" alt="M365 Administrator Expert" class="cert-badge-stat" width="56" height="56" />
      <div class="cert-stat-text">
        <div class="cert-stat-name">M365 Certified</div>
        <div class="cert-stat-title">Administrator Expert</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="cert-stat">
      <img src="/badges/microsoft-certified-associate-badge.svg" alt="Identity & Access Admin Associate" class="cert-badge-stat" width="56" height="56" />
      <div class="cert-stat-text">
        <div class="cert-stat-name">Microsoft Certified</div>
        <div class="cert-stat-title">Identity & Access Admin</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="cert-stat">
      <img src="/badges/microsoft-certified-fundamentals-badge.svg" alt="Azure Fundamentals" class="cert-badge-stat" width="56" height="56" />
      <div class="cert-stat-text">
        <div class="cert-stat-name">Microsoft Certified</div>
        <div class="cert-stat-title">Azure Fundamentals</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="cert-stat">
      <img src="/badges/microsoft-certified-expert-badge.svg" alt="MCSE Productivity Solutions Expert" class="cert-badge-stat" width="56" height="56" />
      <div class="cert-stat-text">
        <div class="cert-stat-name">MCSE</div>
        <div class="cert-stat-title">Productivity Solutions Expert</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="home-tools wrap">
    <div class="page-head">
      <div class="sec-label">// tools</div>
      <h2>Built from real production work.</h2>
      <p>Open source PowerShell tools for Microsoft 365 administrators. Free to use, documented, and published on GitHub.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="home-tools-grid">
      <a href="https://github.com/hiaror/aroramsp-audit-scripts" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="home-tool-card reveal">
        <span class="tool-badge paid">Paid</span>
        <h3>M365 Audit Toolkit</h3>
        <p>Tenant security and mailbox audit. Self-contained HTML reports, certificate-based auth.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="https://github.com/hiaror/graph-exchange-mailbox-cleanup" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="home-tool-card reveal reveal-delay-1">
        <span class="tool-badge free">Free</span>
        <h3>Mailbox Cleanup</h3>
        <p>Graph-based Exchange Online mailbox cleanup. CSV-driven, dry-run supported.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="https://github.com/hiaror/intune-laps-fleet-audit-graph" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="home-tool-card reveal reveal-delay-2">
        <span class="tool-badge free">Free</span>
        <h3>LAPS Fleet Audit</h3>
        <p>Audit Windows LAPS account names at fleet scale using Microsoft Graph.</p>
      </a>
    </div>
    <a href="/tools" class="view-all">view all tools <span class="arrow">→</span></a>
  </section>

  <section class="home-posts wrap">
    <div class="page-head">
      <div class="sec-label">// recent posts</div>
      <h2>From the blog.</h2>
      <p>Field notes from real production work on Microsoft 365, Intune, and Entra ID. Short, practical, no marketing fluff.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="post-list">
      <a href="/blog/powershell-auth-clash" class="post-card reveal reveal-delay-1">
        <div class="post-meta">
          <span>2026-05-10</span>
          <span class="dot"></span>
          <span class="tag">// powershell · m365 · exchange online · microsoft graph</span>
          <span class="dot"></span>
          <span>8 min read</span>
        </div>
        <h3>Microsoft 365 PowerShell authentication failures: three bugs, one fix.</h3>
        <p>The Graph SDK and Exchange Online module fight each other in three different ways: an MSAL assembly clash on PowerShell 5.1, a Graph SDK module load failure when the order is reversed, and a confirmed SDK bug where v2.34+ device-code tokens cache as null. A test matrix across PS 5.1 and PS 7, and the certificate-based fix that works in every order.</p>
        <span class="read">read post <span class="arrow">→</span></span>
      </a>

      <a href="/blog/m365-audit-toolkit" class="post-card reveal reveal-delay-2">
        <div class="post-meta">
          <span>2026-05-09</span>
          <span class="dot"></span>
          <span class="tag">// powershell · m365 · security</span>
          <span class="dot"></span>
          <span>7 min read</span>
        </div>
        <h3>How I Built a PowerShell Toolkit That Audits Your Entire Microsoft 365 Tenant in Minutes</h3>
        <p>Two PowerShell scripts that connect to your tenant via certificate-based app authentication and produce self-contained HTML reports. Tenant audit covers identity, email, endpoint, app registrations, and licensing. Mailbox report shows per-mailbox storage with quota tracking.</p>
        <span class="read">read post <span class="arrow">→</span></span>
      </a>

      <a href="/blog/laps-fleet-audit-graph" class="post-card reveal reveal-delay-3">
        <div class="post-meta">
          <span>2026-05-08</span>
          <span class="dot"></span>
          <span class="tag">// laps · graph</span>
          <span class="dot"></span>
          <span>11 min read</span>
        </div>
        <h3>WLapsAdmin or Administrator? Auditing Windows LAPS at fleet scale.</h3>
        <p>The reason some devices show Administrator instead of WLapsAdmin in the recovery portal is one Windows 11 build number nobody talks about. The end-to-end Microsoft Graph PowerShell audit, with cross-reference, OS eligibility, and the per-device account name lookup Microsoft blocks in bulk.</p>
        <span class="read">read post <span class="arrow">→</span></span>
      </a>

      <a href="/whatido" class="toolkit-promo reveal">
        <span class="badge">New</span>
        <span>· M365 Audit Toolkit: PowerShell scripts for tenant security and mailbox auditing</span>
        <span class="arrow">→</span>
      </a>
    </div>
    <a href="/blog" class="view-all">view all posts <span class="arrow">→</span></a>
  </section>
</Layout>
